fermentation CSA

what is a csa?

CSA (Community Supported Agriculture) is an agricultural model that connects the farmer and consumer directly. CSA Members often will purchase a share of the future harvest at the beginning of the growing season. As farmers harvest throughout the season, members receive their weekly share of fruits and vegetables from the farmer directly.

This model helps the farmers economically at the time of investment and invites the community to witness and respond to their local agricultural ecology. The genius and innovation for this agricultural lineage, like many other regenerative and sustainable agricultural practices, are rooted in Black and Indeginous peoples. Booker T. Whatley, a Tuskegee University professor, popularized this subscription based buyerâ€™s club for small farmers as a technology to generate an agrarian Black middle class. Listening to the words of Leah Penniman of Soul Fire Farm connected me to this history. These technologies that are going to save us are not free.

Reparations are necessary.

Flow $ and land to the Northeast Farmers of Color Land Trust.

interested in becoming a member?

This is a multi-species collaboration, and we are working with microbial rhythms. Yeast and bacteria do not adhere to principles of supply and demand. They listen to their environmental conditions, grow at their own pace, then share their effervescent magic with us. We are so lucky to be in relationship with these invisible-to-the-eye beings. Please be patient with when they can accomadate you as a new member. We have so much to learn from them.

2022 csa memberships

  • 21 Memberships are available for this year. If the CSA is full, you will be placed on a waiting list and notified when a slot becomes available.
  • Pick ups are the last Wednesday of the month 3PM - 7PM.
  • The CSA will be a rotating selection of seasonal kombuchas. Each share is $15 for a 1-liter reusable bottle. Each member can have up to 2 shares.
  • If you do not pick up your share for the month, I unfortunately do not have the space to store your bottle and will drink your share with my loved ones.
  • $5 bottle deposit per bottle. If a bottle is unreturned, lost, or broken, the bottle deposit will be kept an additional deposit will be charged to replace the old bottle. The deposit will be returned when the membership ends.
  • If you would like to end or pause your membership, you must email ampersand.s.paris@gmail.com before the 15th of the month, otherwise, you will still be charged for your share.
  • Special fermentation projects will be available outside of the CSA (think preserved lemons, nocino, hard kombucha, sauerkraut).
